The paper deals with the construction and analysis of Euclidean spanners, which are geometric structures used in various applications. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves analyzing the size and lightness of spanners, which can be viewed as a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper proposes a new construction using Steiner points, which can be seen as a problem in optimization and approximation algorithms (cs.SI).
